          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C fan. Grease and line a 20 x 20 cm square tin. Whisk together the {{cornmeal}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} in a large bowl. In a jug, beat the {{eggs}} with the {{buttermilk}} and melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry and fold together until just combined. The batter should be thick and pourable.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour into the prepared tin and smooth the top. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes until the edges pull away from the tin and a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The top should be a pale golden, not deeply browned. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Serve warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
